Cisco Systems, Inc.
Description of the Company:

Cisco Systems, Inc. is a multinational technology conglomerate headquartered in San Jose, California. Founded in 1984 by Leonard Bosack and Sandy Lerner, Cisco specializes in networking hardware, software, telecommunications equipment, and high-technology services and products. The current CEO is Charles H. Robbins. Cisco is a publicly traded company listed on the NASDAQ under the ticker symbol CSCO​ (Wikipedia)​​ (Encyclopedia Britannica)​.

Products Offered:

Networking Hardware: Routers, switches, and other networking devices.
Software: Cisco IOS, Webex, OpenDNS, and Duo Security.
Telecommunications Equipment: Products for voice, video, and data communication.
Cybersecurity Solutions: Secure access and threat management solutions.
Cloud and Collaboration Tools: Webex and other cloud-based services​ (Wikipedia)​​ (Encyclopedia Britannica)​.

Biggest Competitor:

Cisco's biggest competitors include Huawei, Juniper Networks, and Arista Networks. These companies also specialize in networking and telecommunications equipment and services​ (Encyclopedia Britannica)​.

Last Earnings Report:

For the fiscal year ending July 29, 2023, Cisco reported annual revenue of $55.36 billion with an earnings per share (EPS) of $3.43​ (Encyclopedia Britannica)​.

Stock Price:

As of June 5, 2024, Cisco's stock price was $46.02. Cisco is listed on multiple stock indices, including the Dow Jones Industrial Average and the S&P 500​ (Encyclopedia Britannica)​.

